                    <h1 style="font-weight: bolder;font-size: xx-large;"><u>Why US?</u></h1><br>
                    <img src="drfailover.png" align="center" width="650px" height="350px"><br><br><br>
                    <p style="font-size: x-large;">24/7 continuous operation is critical when doing business on the Internet. Unfortunately, you are vulnerable to all kinds of disasters from hardware failures to network outages which can quickly bring down your web site servers.</p><br><br>
                    <h3>Automatic DR (Disaster/Recovery) Failover Service works by continuously monitoring, testing your web-servers and dynamically updating DNS (Domain Name Service) records.</h3><br><br>
                    <p style="font-size:x-large;"> In event of failure of your primary web-server your visitors will be automatically redirected to the backup web-server. The web-server computers involved in this do not need to be in the same location, reducing vulnerability considerably.</p><br>
                    <p style="font-size: x-large;">You do not need to have your servers with us, you could have two or more servers maintained by different providers in different locations of the world, which would practically eliminate the risk of any one disaster bringing down your web servers. </p>
                    <p style="font-size:x-large;">Another option could be for us to just provide you with generic low-cost web-service as a backup for your primary server, finally making failover protection available even to those with limited IT budgets.</p><br>
                    <p style="font-style: italic;">Note: in order to use this service you will need to have your domain name records maintained by us, so they can be dynamically be updated.</p><br>
